  <result type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved framework conditions for sustainable development</narrative>
   </title>
   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">SSC contributions in 2019 to framework conditions within health in Vietnam: &quot;4 &quot;.

Score from 1-5, 1 lowest and 5 highest.

The planned output targets in the project have generally been met in 2019, but a few have been abandoned.

The majority of planned activities were successfully completed, and the SSC project has provided input and valuable access to relevant fora and high-level meetings at the Vietnamese Ministry of Health with plenty of opportunity to support the primary health care reforms in Vietnam. 

However, the Vietnamese project partners are overwhelmed by the amount of resources required to participate in the SSC project, at the ministry level, as well as in the Thai Binh Province. As of early 2020, the ongoing COVID-19 outbreak has limited progress further, as the outbreak is demanding the full attention of the Vietnamese Ministry of Health and specifically the partner organisation General Department of Preventive Medicine (GDPM).</narrative>
   </description>
